  </div>
  
  <div class="views-field-phpcode">
                <span class="field-content">By the mid-sixteenth century it was customary that at the opening of  Parliament Speakers would request confirmation of the  ‘ancient liberties’ of the Commons, namely freedom of speech and  ‘privilege’ from arrest during sessions. From the beginning of her reign  Elizabeth tried to reserve...</span>
  </div>
  
